# Quality standards (generic)

Apply when implementing UI. Read approved brief from `.cursor/plans/_briefs/` or plan **Brief (approved)** section.

## Universal bar

- **Typography:** Distinct display + readable body; avoid default-only system stacks unless brief says `corporate/minimal-system`.
- **Spacing:** Consistent grid (4/8pt or framework default); no random margins.
- **Color:** One strong accent; avoid generic purple-gradient-on-white unless brief requests it.
- **Motion:** One high-impact moment beats scattered micro-interactions (unless brief `interaction: high`).
- **Accessibility:** Meet brief `a11y` level; minimum touch target 44px on mobile.

## Stack-specific (from brief)

| css_stack | Rules |
|-----------|-------|
| `tailwind` | Utility-first; centralize tokens in `tailwind.config` or CSS variables |
| `bootstrap-css` | Use Bootstrap grid/components; avoid mixing undocumented custom CSS |
| `css-modules` / `scss` | Co-locate styles; no global leakage |
| `styled-components` | Theme provider for colors/spacing |
| `vanilla` | Semantic HTML5; BEM or consistent class naming |

| component_library | Rules |
|-------------------|-------|
| `shadcn-radix` | Use installed shadcn primitives; extend via tokens |
| `mui` / `ant-design` / `chakra` | Follow library theming; no duplicate primitives |
| `bootstrap-components` | react-bootstrap or Bootstrap 5 components |
| `none-custom` | Document component inventory in plan |

## Forbidden (unless brief overrides)

- Inter/Roboto-only typography with no design intent
- Cookie-cutter AI layouts with no brief-aligned aesthetic
- Hardcoded color strings when a token/theme file exists

Design-only work: follow [design-intake/SKILL.md](../skills/design-intake/SKILL.md).
